# Pitcrew Lessons Learned
#
# This file is automatically appended to every mechanic prompt.
# When a pit stop encounters a problem, the crew chief adds a lesson here.
# Each lesson prevents the same mistake from happening again.
#
# Format: LESSON: <what went wrong> → <what to do instead>

LESSON: Git CRLF config causes merge failures on Windows → Always run `git config core.autocrlf false` in the worktree before committing. Or add a .gitattributes with `* text=auto eol=lf`.

LESSON: Constrain the brief — without explicit naming convention rules, the model renamed hyphens to underscores → Add CORRECT/WRONG examples in .pitcrew for naming conventions.
